<TITLE> Announce polls date: pro-Saifur BNP </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 27 (bdnews24.com)  At the electoral reforms dialogue Sunday morning, the reformist faction of the BNP asked the Election Commission to announce the polls date in line with the roadmap. The party also recommended vesting the army personnel on duty during the elections with magisterial authority. "Holding the elections is a great challenge for the Election Commission. Law and order at the grassroots level will have to be further secured ," Mahbubur Rahman, who led the 15-member BNP delegation said at the EC Secretariat. Acting secretary general Hafizuddin Ahmed agreed with the EC proposal of re-designating the electoral constituencies saying: "This amendment in the electoral laws will bring about qualitative change in the political arena." "My party about fully agrees with the EC proposals," he said. bdnews24.
